{"TopicId":178708,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"Setting up a joystick","CreatedByName":"kspguy77","CreatedById":189458,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-03T15:01:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kspguy77","CreatedById":189458,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-03T15:01:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, i have a Logitech Attack\u00A03 joystick and i would like to use it with KSP, but when i put it in one of my laptop\u0027s 3 usb ports, the game doesn\u0027t recognise it.\u00A0 (I\u0027ve tried all of them).There is no issue with the ports. Is there something in the settings i have to tinker with to get it to work? The joystick works fine with Flight Simulator X though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-03T16:01:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you need to go into the settings menu, then input, and there you can assign all the axes and buttons. (mind the axes are on the right side) Then it should work just fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr do you mean the game does not recognize your joystick when you try to asign it in the menu?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-03T16:18:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny chance you\u0027re on Linux?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kspguy77","CreatedById":189458,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-14T10:58:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223461595\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221538582502\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dafni\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/3/2018 at 7:01 PM, Dafni said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you need to go into the settings menu, then input, and there you can assign all the axes and buttons. (mind the axes are on the right side) Then it should work just fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr do you mean the game does not recognize your joystick when you try to asign it in the menu?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe game doesn\u0027t recognize the joystick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-14T12:07:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223487061\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542193094\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189458\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kspguy77\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kspguy77 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe game doesn\u0027t recognize the joystick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds like you are on Linux, right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mod Advanced Fly By Wire might be a solution for you then.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kspguy77","CreatedById":189458,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-07T07:01:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223487083\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542197268\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dafni\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/14/2018 at 2:07 PM, Dafni said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds like you are on Linux, right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mod Advanced Fly By Wire might be a solution for you then.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have Windows 10\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-07T09:42:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223500542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544166095\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189458\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kspguy77\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, kspguy77 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have Windows 10\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI dont know how to help you then, sorry. I have 3 different joysticks here, plus two joypads, and KSP recognizes all axes and buttons no problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry man, I hope somebody with more knowledge jumps in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kroslev Kerman","CreatedById":191310,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-07T11:19:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/189458-kspguy77/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022189458\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/189458-kspguy77/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@kspguy77\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0try the Advanced Fly by wire mod then maybe it will work\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}